com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.method
Interface NativeConstructorCallback

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehavior, NativeCallback, NativeCapable, NativeConstructor
All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeConstructorReflection, NativeDirectConstructorCallback
public interface NativeConstructorCallback
extends NativeCallback, NativeConstructor

The NativeConstructorCallback is the interface implemented by native capable classes that make accessible Java constructors from native. Java constructors are called using Java reflection or normal call.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

Method Detail

onCall

java.lang.Object onCall(java.lang.Object[] args)
Method called after marshalling to Java the native call.

The framework defines a default implementation of this method calling the Java method with reflection or with a normal call.

If the callback is user defined, this method may be overloaded to redefine the default process by the framework, or to intercept the call before the normal process (do not forget call the super method).

Parameters:
args - the arguments passed to the constructor.
Returns:
the new constructed native object.
See Also:
NativeConstructor.call(Object[])
